h3. Issue Summary
* If a user does not have admin access to a workspace and click on the Users on plan link that can be found inside a repository's Users and group access settings, this will cause the left side panel to be duplicated, breaking the UI;

h3. Steps to Reproduce
 # Navigate to a repository to which you have admin access. You cannot have admin access to the workspace where this repository is being hosted;
 # Navigate to the *Repository Settings* > *Users and group access*;
 # Click on the *Users on plan* link;

h3. Expected Results
* User will face a permission error with a working UI;

h3. Actual Results
* The UI breaks duplicating the side panel while displaying the permission error message;


h3. Workaround
* Refreshing the UI makes the side panel go back to normal;

When users create a new branch they are given an option to copy git checkout command with branch name to clipboard. Current command is : 
{{git checkout example-branch}}

But few months ago the command was :
{{git fetch && git checkout example-branch}}

Since new branch was just created, if the user wants to checkout the branch locally, he first needs to run git fetch command, and then paste your checkout command from clipboard.
It would make much more sense to bring back git fetch command.

For organizations with many repositories and potential name collisions, it would save everyone a lot of hassle by simply copying the URL strategy in Bitbucket Server to include the Project KEY.

For example bitbucket/\{workspace-id}/\{project-id}/\{repo}

Right now we have to create dozens of workspaces which isn't fun or easy to manage.  Not to mention that workspace-ids are global and you have to choose something that does not conflict with every workspace on the entire platform.
